    "input": "\"{\\\"title\\\": \\\"Home / X\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://x.com/wiz_io/status/2009272128244207925\\\", \\\"post_analysis\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"The tweet discusses the increasing adoption of MCP and the need for teams to secure how Large Language Models (LLMs) connect to tools and data. It highlights 7 best practices, specifically mentioning locking down supply chains, enforcing least privilege, and adding human oversight.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"bias\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"The tweet has a bias towards emphasizing the urgency and importance of securing LLMs, likely to promote the author's expertise or solutions in this area.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"agenda\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"The author's agenda is to educate their audience on critical security practices for LLMs and to position themselves as a knowledgeable resource, potentially generating interest in their content or services related to LLM security.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"informativeness\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"The tweet is informative as it outlines key best practices for securing LLMs, but it also serves a promotional purpose by hinting at more detailed content ('7 best practices').\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"objectivity\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Promotional\\\\\\\"}\\\", \\\"reply_categories\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"supportive\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"The tweet discusses the increasing adoption of MCP and the need for teams to secure how Large Language Models (LLMs) connect to tools and data.\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"It highlights 7 best practices, specifically mentioning locking down supply chains, enforcing least privilege, and adding human oversight.\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\"dissenting\\\\\\\": [], \\\\\\\"adding_context\\\\\\\": [], \\\\\\\"unrelated\\\\\\\": []}\\\", \\\"image_section\\\": \\\"\\\"}\"",
